column5: Useless post, just excited. Be out soon:)

Well opener sucked due to the river rising another 3 feet over night. But today was really good! No pics and we left after abit because it was obvious the walleye hadn't spawned yet. Lotsa boats did the same, which was nice to see:) so i decided to give my buddy a call and arrange to have my kids and their friends visit the sturgeon hatchery. Turns out that was the right call! Kids had a blast!!!!  Only 5 males and 5 females but the kids learned a lot and got to witness their strength by trying to hold onto their tails, which caused a lot of laughter haha, some good facewashes!!!
Capped off the night bbqing and a bonfire. Awesome times!!!
looks like good times  love the sturgeon photos
Thats awesome….what happened though….your kid lost his face!
Lol i just noticed that! Showed him we had a good laugh:) even tried to adjust it and still no face????? Hahaha weird
Lol i just noticed that! Showed him we had a good laugh:) even tried to adjust it and still no face????? Hahaha weird  Giant face eating Rainy River Sturgeon.
Great to see kids getting up close and personal with the Sturgeon, as they will be the future care takers of our Natural Resourses,   Miigwech for the great report Manitou
Holy moley those are big walleyes!!!!!!!!!
